Comment_contributor: the root is poedȯė = (unit of) ten; the prefix ma (with s short a) means = become.
Ěsa becomes sa when the preceding word ends in an a, e, or o.
Ěpat can become pat, see above. Read: mapoedȯė wo pat
Ěněm can become něm, for the same reason. Read: mapoedȯė wo něm
The root of maatoes is atoes = a hundred
There is no term for ten thousand
